CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 21, 1959, pg. 3, reads: "Admits Killing - Edward Simpson, 31, of 914 Adelaide St., was sentenced to from 10 to 20 years in Western Penitentiary by Judge Henry X. O'Brien who found the man guilty of second-degree murder of 20-year-old Freda Jackson, Oct. 10, 1958, on a hillside near the Breckenridge [Brackenridge] St. steps. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Police officer leading handcuffed Edward Simpson out of courtroom of Judge O'Brien, in Allegheny County Courthouse
